This container bundles and/or depends on several third-party projects. Each
is listed below with its license. By installing and running this plugin, you
agree to comply with each of those licenses.

1. ai-captcha-bypass (reCAPTCHA v2 reference) — https://github.com/aydinnyunus/ai-captcha-bypass
   License: custom permissive ("attribution + no-warranty")
   Usage: the `recaptcha_v2.py` solver is a reimplementation inspired by the
   reference `recaptcha_v2_test` flow. No source is copied verbatim; the
   structure (instruction extraction → parallel tile classification → click
   → verify loop) is the attributed concept.

3. Turnstile-Solver (Theyka) — https://github.com/Theyka/Turnstile-Solver
   License: NOASSERTION (source-available)
   Usage: the `turnstile.py` flow was adapted from Theyka's patchright-based
   checkbox-click logic, re-expressed against Camoufox. No source is copied
   verbatim.

4. camoufox — https://github.com/daijro/camoufox
   License: MPL-2.0
   Usage: runtime stealth browser. MPL-2.0 is weak copyleft at the
   file level — our code does not modify camoufox itself, so no MPL
   obligations propagate to this plugin.

5. patchright — https://github.com/Kaliiiiiiiiii-Vinyzu/patchright
   License: Apache-2.0
   Usage: pulled in transitively via hcaptcha-challenger. Clean attribution.

Summary: the effective license of this plugin container is **permissive**.
All runtime dependencies are MIT, Apache 2.0, MPL-2.0, or source-available.
hCaptcha solving is now handled in-house (src/solvers/hcaptcha.py) via a
custom VLM-driven flow that does not rely on any copyleft library.
